    answer: "The teach‑back method involves asking the patient to repeat information or instructions in their own words after education is provided. It confirms understanding and allows the nurse to correct misconceptions immediately. In patients with limited English proficiency, it:\n- Identifies gaps when interpreter services are used.\n- Reduces the risk of medication errors and readmission.\n- Aligns with NMBA standards (Standard 1 – Professional Practice) and the Australian Commission on Safety and Quality in Health Care’s ‘National Safety and Quality Health Service Standards’ (Standard 4 – Medication safety).\nImplementation steps:\n1. Provide information using plain language and visual aids.\n2. Ask, “Can you tell me in your own words how you will take this medication?”\n3. Clarify and repeat as needed.\n4. Document the patient’s response and any additional teaching provided.",
