    answer: "• **AHPRA Code of Conduct (Standard 3 – Culturally safe practice):**\n  - Recognise the patient’s cultural values, belief systems, and family dynamics.\n  - Obtain informed consent using an interpreter and ensure the patient understands treatment options.\n• **Cultural Safety Framework (NSW Health, 2021):**\n  - Conduct a cultural assessment (e.g., using the ‘Cultural Safety Checklist’) to identify trauma, migration stressors, and support networks.\n  - Incorporate collectivist decision‑making by involving family or community elders where appropriate, while respecting patient autonomy.\n• **Documentation:**\n  - Record the interpreter’s name, language, and date/time of use.\n  - Document cultural assessment findings, identified support persons, and any modifications to care plans (e.g., gender‑specific therapist, use of culturally appropriate psycho‑education materials).\n  - Note consent process and any cultural‑specific concerns raised.\nThese steps satisfy AHPRA’s requirement for safe, respectful, and competent practice and support the nurse’s legal and ethical obligations under the *Health Practitioner Regulation National Law Act*.",
